    <chapter id="using-kbattleship">
    <title>Using KBattleship</title>
    <para>
        If you want to play KBattleship, you will need two players as it is a network game only. One Player has to
        open the game via <guimenuitem>"Start Server"</guimenuitem> (F3). A dialogbox opens which will ask
        you for for a nickname and a port. Normally, KBattleship will suggest your login name but you can enter any
        string you want. The predefined port should be ok. However, if you encounter problems, you can choose any
        other free ports above 1024. Note that you need to inform the other player when you use a different port then
        the default as he/she needs to set it, too.
    </para>
    <para>
        The other player has to choose <guimenuitem>"Connect to Server"</guimenuitem> (F2). Again, a nickname
        is suggested, but you can choose any name you like. An important point is the field "Host". Here, you have to
        enter the host name of the server (the machine of the player that inicitated the game). This can either be a name
        from your hosts file ("foobar"), a internet host name ("foo.bar.org") or an IP-Address ("192.168.0.10") of the host
        you want to connect to.
    </para>
    <para>
        When you are done, you can start the game. Simply follow the instructions in the statusbar. It will issue hints
        and suggest what to do next. When you now look at the screen, you will find two grid fields, the so-called
        "battle areas". The left area belongs to you. This is where you place your ships and where you can follow
        the military actions of your enemy. The right area is where your enemys fleet is located. When it's your turn
        to fire, you need to click on a certain sector (a field if the battle area) where you suppose the ships to be
        located.
    </para>
    <para>
        First, you need to place your ships. The game iniciator starts. When he/she is done,
        player 2 sets his/her ships. Ship placement is very easy: Simply click on the field where you want to place
        your ship. The first one will have a lenght of 4, the next will be 3 fields long etc. Click on the field where you
        want to start the placement. If you click with the <mousebutton>left</mousebutton> mousebutton, the field
        will be placed horizotally, a <mousebutton>right</mousebutton> click will cause it to be placed vertically.
    </para>
    <para>
        Now you can blindly fire on the enemy battle area :). The statusbar indicates who is about to shoot. A player
        may shoot until he hits the water. Then, the other player is on the turn.
    </para>
  </chapter>

  <chapter id="questionsanswersandtips">
